WEBVTT

00:17.440 --> 00:19.120
NARRATOR:
Some prodigious children

00:19.120 --> 00:21.400
display a gift for music.

00:24.040 --> 00:28.640
Others for chess or spelling.

00:30.160 --> 00:32.040
Even at an early age,

00:32.040 --> 00:36.880
Matilda had a keenly developed
interest in murder --

00:36.880 --> 00:39.720
not, it must be said,
in the committing of them...

00:39.720 --> 00:41.240
[ Doorbell jingles ]

00:41.240 --> 00:43.120
...but in the solving.

00:46.960 --> 00:50.640
With her mother missing
and her paternity unknown,

00:50.640 --> 00:52.440
Matilda occasionally wondered

00:52.440 --> 00:54.960
what it would be like
to have a father.

00:59.920 --> 01:01.120
[ Doorbell jingles ]

01:04.879 --> 01:08.640
But despite her early aptitude
for the art of detection,

01:08.640 --> 01:11.880
some small part of her knew
that certain questions

01:11.880 --> 01:14.080
were better left unasked...

01:16.240 --> 01:18.160
...and unanswered.

02:20.280 --> 02:22.320
[ Bell chiming,
birds chirping ]

02:24.240 --> 02:25.520
[ Bird caws ]

02:27.480 --> 02:28.320
Sir.

02:29.760 --> 02:31.720
I have an important case
for you, Stone.

02:31.720 --> 02:34.160
Inspector Thorne believed
that everything in life

02:34.160 --> 02:35.600
has to be earned.

02:35.600 --> 02:37.320
Ringo the dachshund is missing.

02:37.320 --> 02:39.600
But having solved
a double murder

02:39.600 --> 02:41.240
so early in her career...

02:41.240 --> 02:43.480
Not high-profile enough?

02:43.480 --> 02:47.280
...Matilda now needed
bringing down a peg or two.

02:47.280 --> 02:49.080
A zero-tolerance policy, sir.

02:49.080 --> 02:51.040
Very sound policing.
I'm all over it.

02:52.280 --> 02:53.360
Right.

03:01.160 --> 03:03.880
Precisely eight miles,
four yards,

03:03.880 --> 03:05.600
and two inches away,

03:05.600 --> 03:09.920
in the private recording studio
of rock legend Sir Ray Ives,

03:09.920 --> 03:11.440
drummer Viv Collins

03:11.440 --> 03:15.120
was surfacing from her
all-too-familiar nightmare.

03:21.200 --> 03:22.400
Kumquat.

03:22.400 --> 03:24.520
And where more sensitive souls

03:24.520 --> 03:28.120
preferred silence in the wake
of a raging hangover,

03:28.120 --> 03:31.000
Viv had always favored
picking up her sticks.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.560
Oh, God.

03:34.600 --> 03:36.640
[ Sighing ]

03:38.880 --> 03:39.880
Meanwhile...

03:39.880 --> 03:41.800
[ Drums playing ]

03:41.800 --> 03:45.760
Meanwhile, across from
the studio in the main house,

03:45.760 --> 03:48.440
one half of perhaps
the most ill-matched couple

03:48.440 --> 03:53.280
in southern England
was suddenly gripped by regret.

03:54.360 --> 03:57.920
LEN: I -- Uh, yeah,
it's a message for Steven.

03:57.920 --> 03:59.680
We've arrived.
Everything's cool.

03:59.680 --> 04:02.000
We're ready to get rocking
in the studio,

04:02.000 --> 04:04.240
so to speak,
so call me back.

04:04.240 --> 04:07.040
It's Len. Savage.

04:07.040 --> 04:10.000
I should never have let you
persuade me to come.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.400
Really?
You're doing this?

04:12.400 --> 04:15.360
We haven't put out an album
for 10 years.

04:15.360 --> 04:18.120
No one's interested in us,
not anymore,

04:18.120 --> 04:21.160
and we're still called
Volcanic Youth.

04:21.160 --> 04:23.440
It's embarrassing.

04:23.440 --> 04:27.800
You know, I worked my ass off
to get this deal.

04:27.800 --> 04:31.600
I thought you'd be over the moon
like everyone else, but...

04:31.600 --> 04:33.880
Anyway, it's too late
to change your mind.

04:33.880 --> 04:36.000
The deal's already been done.

04:37.240 --> 04:39.840
And you'd hold me to that?

04:39.840 --> 04:42.240
Well, as your husband,
maybe not.

04:42.240 --> 04:45.400
But as your manager,
yeah, I will.

04:52.280 --> 04:55.360
MATILDA: And when
did you last see Ringo?

05:00.040 --> 05:03.400
Well, he vanished this morning
in the woods

05:03.400 --> 05:04.880
on the edge of town.

05:04.880 --> 05:07.120
[ Mid-tempo rock music playing]

05:09.920 --> 05:12.560
-It's true, then.
-What is?

05:12.560 --> 05:15.440
That Volcanic Youth
are recording a reunion record

05:15.440 --> 05:16.680
up at Trent House.

05:20.640 --> 05:22.280
Ringo loved their music.

05:23.280 --> 05:24.840
[ Water dripping ]

05:24.840 --> 05:27.720
Where most would
hear only silence,

05:27.720 --> 05:30.840
Kurt Lee picked up on the slow
drip of a bathroom tap...

05:30.840 --> 05:32.160
[ Fly buzzing ]

05:32.160 --> 05:34.040
...a buzzing fly
caught in a web...

05:34.040 --> 05:35.560
[ Bird caws ]

05:35.560 --> 05:38.600
...and the low croak
of a distant raven.

05:38.600 --> 05:40.440
[ Mid-tempo rock music playing
in distance]

05:53.320 --> 05:57.360
After 33 years of
varying degrees of fame,

05:57.360 --> 05:59.480
Electra Bliss
was still committed

05:59.480 --> 06:04.160
to making a grand entrance
whenever humanly possible.

06:05.800 --> 06:08.480
Well, hello, you lovely people.

06:08.480 --> 06:10.640
[ Chuckles ]

06:10.640 --> 06:14.480
To be clear, I did want to
give you all a ride in the limo,

06:14.480 --> 06:16.360
but spoilsport Len
wouldn't allow it.

06:16.360 --> 06:18.440
Well, you lot are like
the royal family.

06:18.440 --> 06:21.040
I can't risk you all
traveling together, can I?

06:27.040 --> 06:29.000
Hope you got my arrival,
Jonas.

06:30.600 --> 06:33.000
It was Jonas Wimmer's
firm belief

06:33.000 --> 06:35.120
that despite
the relative obscurity

06:35.120 --> 06:37.160
of the now mostly forgotten

06:37.160 --> 06:39.560
new-wave rock band
Volcanic Youth,

06:39.560 --> 06:42.560
his film about them
was destined to clean up

06:42.560 --> 06:45.600
at a future awards season.

06:45.600 --> 06:48.320
And so he had dedicated himself
to interviewing

06:48.320 --> 06:51.160
the remaining members
of the band and their manager.

06:51.160 --> 06:52.960
Um, could you take
your glasses off?

06:52.960 --> 06:54.000
No.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.880
Although his style
was less fly-on-the-wall

06:59.880 --> 07:01.880
than fly-in-your-face.

07:01.880 --> 07:04.040
Give it a rest, Jonas.

07:05.440 --> 07:07.040
[ Gargling ]

07:08.320 --> 07:09.720
Oh.

07:09.720 --> 07:11.680
I see
you still got the jacket.

07:11.680 --> 07:12.960
[ Plays notes ]

07:12.960 --> 07:16.160
One previous owner --
Janis Joplin.

07:16.160 --> 07:17.200
I got it when "Twenty Seven"

07:17.200 --> 07:19.160
reached number three
in the charts.

07:19.160 --> 07:22.160
Worn it for luck ever since.

07:22.160 --> 07:25.000
I'm surprised it hasn't
finally fallen apart by now.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.960
[ Laughs ]

07:26.960 --> 07:29.160
I look after things
that are important to me.

07:29.160 --> 07:30.960
-Unlike some people.
-[ Smooches ]

07:30.960 --> 07:33.040
-[ Gargles ]
-[ Imitates gargling ]

07:34.760 --> 07:39.320
♪ I will sing every sorrow
under the sun♪

07:39.320 --> 07:40.920
Aunt Cat?

07:42.560 --> 07:45.200
♪ I couldn't take
all your worries♪

07:45.200 --> 07:50.160
♪ Away from you, my love♪

07:50.160 --> 07:51.600
Cat?

07:51.600 --> 07:53.000
♪ Even sometimes
in the summer♪

07:53.000 --> 07:55.200
Oh, hello, kid.

07:55.200 --> 07:57.360
[ Volume lowers]

07:58.840 --> 07:59.880
Everything all right?

08:03.840 --> 08:07.080
I just heard
Volcanic Youth are recording

08:07.080 --> 08:09.520
up at Sir Ray Ives' studio.

08:12.280 --> 08:14.360
[ Cheers and applause]

08:14.360 --> 08:17.520
Matilda knew that despite
some early promise,

08:17.520 --> 08:19.680
Cat's involvement
with Volcanic Youth

08:19.680 --> 08:22.440
had ended
for a number of reasons...

08:27.880 --> 08:29.680
...the most significant
of which

08:29.680 --> 08:31.280
was her becoming pregnant

08:31.280 --> 08:35.159
after a misjudged drunken
encounter with a doting fan.

08:38.559 --> 08:42.360
This broke the heart
of her first great love,

08:42.360 --> 08:45.800
caused irreparable rifts
in the band,

08:45.800 --> 08:50.240
and would result, seven months,
four days, and one hour later,

08:50.240 --> 08:51.960
in Cat being unable
to commit

08:51.960 --> 08:53.440
to a make-or-break tour

08:53.440 --> 08:57.520
of the dive bars and beer halls
of Western Europe.

08:57.520 --> 09:00.120
I'm sorry, I can't.

09:00.120 --> 09:02.320
Not like this.

09:02.320 --> 09:04.600
She's right.
She looks like a whale.

09:06.720 --> 09:09.080
Oh, who cares?

09:09.080 --> 09:11.920
Volcanic Youth stopped
being relevant years ago.

09:15.360 --> 09:17.040
Cuppa?

09:22.480 --> 09:25.160
Only later,
when Matilda had gone,

09:25.160 --> 09:27.920
would Cat's bravado subside,

09:27.920 --> 09:30.600
and she'd once again
entertain thoughts

09:30.600 --> 09:32.920
of what might have been,

09:32.920 --> 09:34.280
both musically...

09:34.280 --> 09:36.680
[ Note reverberates ]

09:36.680 --> 09:38.960
...and with the woman
she had once envisaged

09:38.960 --> 09:41.200
spending her life with.

09:45.560 --> 09:47.800
Ringo!

09:47.800 --> 09:49.760
Ringo, come on!

09:49.760 --> 09:50.720
[ Whistling ]

09:52.480 --> 09:54.200
Ringo!

09:57.400 --> 10:00.160
JANE: Are you sure
you want to do this, Cat?

10:00.160 --> 10:02.040
CAT:
I'll be fine.

10:13.680 --> 10:14.560
[ Intercom buzzes ]

10:18.680 --> 10:21.960
Despite Cat's determination
to rebuild bridges

10:21.960 --> 10:23.800
with her former bandmates,

10:23.800 --> 10:29.280
her sisters, Beth and Jane,
saw only troubled waters ahead.

10:29.280 --> 10:31.600
I'm not sure this is
such a good idea.

10:31.600 --> 10:34.040
-Because of Nikki?
-Yeah.

10:35.800 --> 10:37.360
JONAS:
So tell me about Nikki.

10:37.360 --> 10:41.800
Well, Volcanic Youth was, um...

10:41.800 --> 10:43.640
Well, it was Nikki's idea,
you know?

10:43.640 --> 10:48.280
And we were young women,
and it was a man's world,

10:48.280 --> 10:52.600
and we had so much
that we wanted to say.

10:52.600 --> 10:54.040
[ Chuckles ]

10:54.040 --> 10:56.560
Yeah, well, you know,
everything changed.

10:56.560 --> 10:58.960
Cat left, and then Nikki...

11:01.520 --> 11:02.920
Yeah.

11:02.920 --> 11:05.520
JONAS: Nikki drowned
in your manager's swimming pool

11:05.520 --> 11:08.160
back in 1985.

11:08.160 --> 11:10.400
Look, just because
you die at 27,

11:10.400 --> 11:13.080
it doesn't automatically
make you a genius.

11:16.760 --> 11:18.680
I didn't believe it
when they told me

11:18.680 --> 11:20.480
who was waiting at the gate.

11:22.040 --> 11:24.760
Hey, Len.
How are you?

11:24.760 --> 11:29.080
Oh, you know, older, uglier,

11:29.080 --> 11:31.160
still not as rich as
I'd like to be,

11:31.160 --> 11:35.000
but, hey, that's life.

11:39.720 --> 11:41.080
Come.

11:43.880 --> 11:47.160
♪ Oh, the wheels of time ♪

11:47.160 --> 11:49.680
Oh, it's like the studio
time forgot.

11:49.680 --> 11:54.280
Yeah, the label thought it would
add authenticity to the album.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.800
-Hey.
-Hi.

11:55.800 --> 11:58.680
Cat, this is Kurt Lee.

11:58.680 --> 12:00.920
-Hiya.
-Big fan, Miss Stone.

12:00.920 --> 12:03.640
I loved the first two
Volcanic Youth albums.

12:03.640 --> 12:07.400
Your -- Sorry, your bass,
so raw, so urgent.

12:07.400 --> 12:09.000
How do you capture
that kind of energy?

12:09.000 --> 12:12.920
Oh, no time, a bit of luck, and
very limited musical ability.

12:14.040 --> 12:17.400
♪ Time's past,
but now I'm home ♪

12:17.400 --> 12:21.520
♪ 'Cause, baby,
there's no stopping me ♪

12:21.520 --> 12:25.160
♪ Now I'm back to where
I'm known ♪

12:25.160 --> 12:28.680
♪ So let's dance,
don't stop to sleep ♪

12:28.680 --> 12:31.520
♪ We're soaring high ♪

12:31.520 --> 12:33.800
Hey, guys.
Might want to take a break.

12:33.800 --> 12:36.080
We have a visitor.

12:37.480 --> 12:38.320
[ Gasps ]

12:41.720 --> 12:43.240
Who's that?

12:43.240 --> 12:45.720
[ Whistling ]

13:09.920 --> 13:11.240
[ Whistling ]

13:36.720 --> 13:38.760
[ Sighs ]

13:38.760 --> 13:40.840
[ Ringtone plays ]

13:42.400 --> 13:43.880
The Sound & the Fury.

13:43.880 --> 13:46.360
MATILDA:
Mr. Cardosa, it's D.S. Stone.

13:46.360 --> 13:48.080
I have some bad news.

13:51.400 --> 13:53.440
I can't believe
Cat Stone is actually

13:53.440 --> 13:56.560
hanging in the studio with us.

13:56.560 --> 13:58.480
TALLULAH:
You still play much?

13:58.480 --> 13:59.760
No, not really.

13:59.760 --> 14:01.080
Focused on my writing.

14:01.080 --> 14:03.440
Oh, those graphic novels
of yours.

14:03.440 --> 14:05.080
I've read a few.

14:05.080 --> 14:07.280
-They're good.
-GINA: [ Clears throat ]

14:07.280 --> 14:09.560
So does that mean
I'm still safe, you know,

14:09.560 --> 14:11.120
as the new bassist?

14:11.120 --> 14:13.360
-Yeah, you're safe.
-Good.

14:13.360 --> 14:15.280
You know,
I was trying to remember, Cat,

14:15.280 --> 14:17.240
when the last time was
that I saw you,

14:17.240 --> 14:18.760
and then I realized
that it was...

14:19.720 --> 14:22.240
It was, um, when --

14:22.240 --> 14:26.880
when Nikki was
still the lead singer.

14:26.880 --> 14:29.560
This regrettable reference
to Nikki Holler

14:29.560 --> 14:33.120
would cast a long shadow
over the reunion.

14:33.120 --> 14:35.040
I need a fag.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.080
Should we take a break?

14:45.120 --> 14:48.320
Part of our revival,
apparently.

14:48.320 --> 14:49.840
-The price of fame, I guess.
-Hmm.

14:52.680 --> 14:55.560
So, what's your sprog doing now?

14:57.480 --> 15:01.080
Oh, you know, the usual.

15:01.080 --> 15:02.680
You don't know, do you?

15:02.680 --> 15:05.120
Actually, it's really good
'cause it makes it

15:05.120 --> 15:08.640
so much easier
for me to forgive you.

15:08.640 --> 15:10.120
Forgive me?
What the hell for?

15:10.120 --> 15:12.480
For bailing on us.
The tour.

15:12.480 --> 15:13.600
Bailing?

15:13.600 --> 15:15.640
You couldn't wait
to get me out the door.

15:15.640 --> 15:17.680
And you couldn't wait
to be a mother.

15:17.680 --> 15:20.880
You even left Nikki
in the dust.

15:20.880 --> 15:22.520
You need to apologize.

15:22.520 --> 15:24.560
Never apologize.

15:24.560 --> 15:26.280
Never explain.

15:27.840 --> 15:29.320
-You're a bloody cow!
-Ow!

15:29.320 --> 15:31.240
-Uh-oh.
-Get off me, you crazy woman!

15:31.240 --> 15:34.200
You'll never bloody change!
You won't never, ever, ever!

15:34.200 --> 15:35.360
-Girls, girls, girls!
-Crazy woman!

15:35.360 --> 15:37.200
-Whoa, whoa!
-ELECTRA: She needs help.

15:37.200 --> 15:38.040
LEN: Yeah.

15:42.520 --> 15:43.680
[ Exhales sharply ]

15:46.480 --> 15:48.160
Well, that went well, then.

15:55.560 --> 15:58.920
As Volcanic Youth
and their entourage waited

15:58.920 --> 16:02.600
to meet the legendary
and somewhat reclusive owner

16:02.600 --> 16:04.400
of Trent House Studios,

16:04.400 --> 16:07.320
familiar tensions
began to surface.

16:07.320 --> 16:11.000
Uh, just water.
Thanks all the same.

16:11.000 --> 16:13.040
I can smell booze on you.

16:16.720 --> 16:18.680
SIR RAY: Namaste.

16:23.120 --> 16:24.240
I'm Sir Ray.

16:25.560 --> 16:27.640
Welcome.

16:27.640 --> 16:30.120
The outlook
of rock god Sir Ray Ives

16:30.120 --> 16:33.160
had been completely altered
during an extended stay

16:33.160 --> 16:37.760
at a Goan ashram
during the mid-'70s.

16:37.760 --> 16:41.480
The Scarlet King would
never perform onstage again,

16:41.480 --> 16:43.800
instead retreating
to the studio

16:43.800 --> 16:48.120
and the temptations
of the double album.

16:48.120 --> 16:54.160
I've never believed you have to
suffer to write great songs,

16:54.160 --> 16:57.240
as long as the emotion
is genuine.

16:57.240 --> 16:59.640
GINA: Mm, and people
can relate, right?

16:59.640 --> 17:02.920
Film's the same.
It's all emotion.

17:02.920 --> 17:05.839
ELECTRA: It's the same for me,
Sir Ray.

17:05.839 --> 17:08.440
Helps me to remember
where I'm from.

17:08.440 --> 17:10.000
I delve into that a lot.

17:10.000 --> 17:12.400
Might need to delve
a little deeper.

17:12.400 --> 17:16.359
'Cause the last album was,
you know, not up to much.

17:18.160 --> 17:21.319
So why did you stop touring,
Sir Ray?

17:21.319 --> 17:22.640
Yeah, don't you miss
playing live?

17:22.640 --> 17:26.640
My songs are like children
to me.

17:26.640 --> 17:31.400
Nowadays I'd rather not expose
them to the world like that.

17:31.400 --> 17:33.960
I would have loved
a few nippers myself.

17:34.760 --> 17:37.120
Oh! What?

17:37.120 --> 17:40.680
Years and years of nappies
and school plays

17:40.680 --> 17:41.960
and teenaged angst?

17:41.960 --> 17:43.760
Ha!
Can't imagine anything worse.

17:43.760 --> 17:45.360
Quelle surprise.

17:45.360 --> 17:46.840
Motherhood would mean
she'd have to

17:46.840 --> 17:48.760
think of someone
other than herself for once.

17:48.760 --> 17:50.280
Who wants another drink?

17:50.280 --> 17:52.480
Just ignore her, Sir Ray.
She's bitter.

17:52.480 --> 17:55.640
And she's bankrupt poor Len
over the IVF bill.

17:55.640 --> 17:57.080
Shh.

17:58.400 --> 18:00.160
Touchy subject?

18:00.160 --> 18:01.640
At least I'm not
lying to myself

18:01.640 --> 18:03.360
that I'm still
some kind of star.

18:03.360 --> 18:04.840
Rather a fading a star

18:04.840 --> 18:08.160
than a housewife
with nothing but regrets.

18:10.640 --> 18:13.120
Maybe you should have
married her.

18:13.120 --> 18:15.080
You'd have made
a lovely couple.

18:15.080 --> 18:17.560
Oh!

18:17.560 --> 18:18.640
Come on.
[ Sighs ]

18:18.640 --> 18:20.080
[ Chuckling ]

18:28.480 --> 18:29.920
[ Squeaks ]

18:32.520 --> 18:34.600
[ Sobbing ] Ringo.

18:34.600 --> 18:36.160
Ringo.

18:37.040 --> 18:38.960
♪ Remember me ♪

18:38.960 --> 18:42.560
♪ 'Cause that's all you've got ♪

18:42.560 --> 18:44.840
Yes.

18:44.840 --> 18:47.400
♪ I'm a road ♪

18:47.400 --> 18:50.320
♪ That don't go home ♪

18:50.320 --> 18:51.400
Hmm.

18:53.720 --> 18:56.000
Fading star?
Hmm.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.160
You've still got it, baby.

19:02.200 --> 19:03.840
[ Door opens ]

19:03.840 --> 19:05.640
[ Thunder rumbling ]

19:10.560 --> 19:14.680
♪ Oh, the reason ♪

19:14.680 --> 19:18.200
♪ For my floods of tears ♪

19:18.200 --> 19:20.600
♪ Is 'cause you say ♪

19:20.600 --> 19:26.000
♪ We're surely dying ♪

19:26.680 --> 19:30.120
♪ Remember me ♪

19:30.120 --> 19:33.600
♪ 'Cause that's
all you've got ♪

19:33.600 --> 19:36.920
♪ 'Cause I'm a road ♪

19:36.920 --> 19:40.520
♪ That don't go home ♪

19:40.520 --> 19:41.920
[ Electricity crackles,
music stops ]

19:41.920 --> 19:43.760
[ Clapping ]

19:45.480 --> 19:47.640
Kurt?

19:47.640 --> 19:50.000
Kurt, stop messing about.

19:51.080 --> 19:53.040
Kurt, is that you?

19:57.080 --> 19:58.680
-Kurt, this isn't funny.
-[ Electricity crackles ]

20:05.720 --> 20:07.080
-[ Thud ]
-[ Grunts ]

20:07.080 --> 20:09.520
[ Whimpering ]

20:09.520 --> 20:10.760
[ Whimpering stops ]

20:14.040 --> 20:15.800
[ Police radio chatter ]

20:25.560 --> 20:27.160
Terry.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.040
The scene is secure,
and I've asked everyone

20:33.040 --> 20:34.440
who's still here
to wait in the main house.

20:34.440 --> 20:36.240
Everyone who's still here?

20:36.240 --> 20:38.200
One of the band
left in the night.

20:40.920 --> 20:42.040
Okay.

20:43.440 --> 20:44.960
[ Sighs ]

20:58.480 --> 21:00.600
Despite the countless
crime scenes

21:00.600 --> 21:03.880
that Matilda had created
during her childhood,

21:03.880 --> 21:07.960
the real thing still played
havoc with her equilibrium.

21:11.560 --> 21:13.640
-DANIEL: Hi.
-[ Gasps ]

21:13.640 --> 21:16.720
-Daniel.
-Oh. Sorry.

21:16.720 --> 21:19.120
Sorry, I'm a quiet walker.
Should have knocked.

21:20.920 --> 21:23.000
Oh, bloody hell.

21:23.000 --> 21:25.120
Well, there goes
my teenage years.

21:25.120 --> 21:27.200
Had a huge crush
on Electra Bliss.

21:27.200 --> 21:29.880
She knew it was unreasonable,
given the situation,

21:29.880 --> 21:31.600
but the idea of Dr. Lynch

21:31.600 --> 21:33.720
having feelings
for Electra Bliss,

21:33.720 --> 21:37.320
even way back, caused Matilda
to think bad thoughts.

21:40.480 --> 21:42.720
Excuse the outfit.
Came straight here.

21:42.720 --> 21:44.760
So, what have we got?

21:44.760 --> 21:47.240
The deceased, Susan Foyle --
aka Electra Bliss --

21:47.240 --> 21:49.400
was 50 or 55,
depending on the source,

21:49.400 --> 21:51.200
and lead singer
of Volcanic Youth.

21:51.200 --> 21:53.640
They're a new-wave band
from the '80s.

21:53.640 --> 21:55.160
Their biggest hit
was "Blue Girl,"

21:55.160 --> 21:56.680
which was used
in a jean commercial.

21:56.680 --> 21:58.080
♪ La, la, la ♪

21:58.080 --> 21:59.680
♪ There's a blue girl
over here ♪

21:59.680 --> 22:03.520
♪ And she's giving me
the fits ♪

22:03.520 --> 22:05.480
I think I vaguely
remember them.

22:05.480 --> 22:06.960
Last seen alive?

22:08.480 --> 22:10.680
According to their manager,

22:10.680 --> 22:14.760
she retired alone
to bed at midnight.

22:15.600 --> 22:17.280
Any thought
on time of death yet?

22:17.280 --> 22:18.680
Need longer to be accurate,

22:18.680 --> 22:20.680
but I'd estimate
between 1:00 and 4:00 a.m.

22:20.680 --> 22:23.760
-Who are your lead suspects?
-Everyone who we know was here.

22:23.760 --> 22:26.280
Tallulah Savage-Hughes, keyboard
player and wife of the manager,

22:26.280 --> 22:28.560
left in the night
and remains unaccounted for.

22:28.560 --> 22:30.640
Her phone's off, so we've been
unable to track it,

22:30.640 --> 22:32.520
but there's an ANPR out
on her car.

22:32.520 --> 22:34.240
Very good.

22:34.240 --> 22:36.040
You can put the missing-dog
investigation on hold for now.

22:36.040 --> 22:37.960
Dead dog, I'm afraid, sir.

22:37.960 --> 22:39.440
Run over.

22:39.440 --> 22:42.360
Oh.
Poor thing.

22:42.360 --> 22:44.440
Well, we need
to focus our resources,

22:44.440 --> 22:45.880
and I want zero interference
from your aunts.

22:45.880 --> 22:47.160
Do I make myself clear?

22:47.160 --> 22:49.320
As a tubular bell, sir.

22:49.320 --> 22:52.760
What Inspector Thorne
wanted to say next was...

23:06.920 --> 23:08.480
Oh, world,

23:08.480 --> 23:11.600
no world
but mass of public wrongs,

23:11.600 --> 23:15.120
confused and filled
with murder and misdeeds.

23:17.160 --> 23:19.320
But what
he actually said was...

23:19.320 --> 23:20.560
Better get to work, then, Stone.

23:22.640 --> 23:24.360
Let's take a look
at her room.

23:38.840 --> 23:41.080
-I'll, uh, see you inside.
-Okay.

23:49.000 --> 23:50.680
[ Cellphone rings ]

23:54.760 --> 23:56.680
I'm a bit busy, Aunt Beth.
Can I call you back?

23:56.680 --> 23:58.880
-Are you at Trent House?
-I might be.

23:58.880 --> 24:00.800
The sister of the cleaner there

24:00.800 --> 24:03.200
just told me
there's been a murder.

24:03.200 --> 24:04.720
Of course she did.

24:22.000 --> 24:24.160
Someone was in here with her.

24:29.680 --> 24:32.080
And this has been wiped down
in a hurry.

24:43.520 --> 24:44.600
[ Switch clicks ]

24:56.440 --> 24:59.200
Drilled from this side recently.

25:06.080 --> 25:08.040
She was being watched.

25:11.960 --> 25:15.480
My horoscope said that this week
would end on a bad note,

25:15.480 --> 25:18.240
but I thought it meant,
like, you know, musically.

25:18.240 --> 25:20.600
About time.

25:20.600 --> 25:22.200
I'm Detective Sergeant Stone,

25:22.200 --> 25:23.800
and I'm in charge
of the investigation.

25:23.800 --> 25:25.360
Right, hi.

25:25.360 --> 25:28.120
My name's Len Savage,
manager of the band.

25:28.120 --> 25:29.960
You should speak to me first
before the media

25:29.960 --> 25:32.280
gets hold of this
and arrives at the gate.

25:32.280 --> 25:34.560
Can we stop word getting out?

25:34.560 --> 25:36.080
Well, it would help
if none of you

25:36.080 --> 25:37.560
posted anything
on social media.

25:37.560 --> 25:40.400
Whoa, whoa, hang on.

25:40.400 --> 25:42.120
Susan's fans have the right
to know what's happened.

25:42.120 --> 25:43.520
Her fans?!

25:43.520 --> 25:46.400
What about my right
to some privacy in my own home?!

25:46.400 --> 25:49.400
You can't suppress the truth,
old man!

25:49.400 --> 25:51.560
Truth?!
[ Chuckling ] Yeah, right.

25:51.560 --> 25:54.760
Okay, let's all try
to keep calm.

25:54.760 --> 25:57.400
We'll need a copy of any footage
you've shot since arriving here.

25:57.400 --> 26:02.200
Ommmm.

26:02.200 --> 26:04.280
Uh, I wasn't allowed to shoot
last night,

26:04.280 --> 26:05.240
so I doubt
it's much use to you.

26:05.240 --> 26:06.560
I'll be the judge of that.

26:06.560 --> 26:08.800
Ommmm.

26:08.800 --> 26:12.000
Have you heard from your wife
since she left?

26:12.000 --> 26:13.760
Ommmm.

26:13.760 --> 26:15.920
Did anything take place between
her and the deceased last night?

26:18.240 --> 26:19.800
Tallulah had a barney
with Electra

26:19.800 --> 26:21.560
and then
went storming off.

26:21.560 --> 26:23.600
Well, you were right,
Mr. Savage.

26:23.600 --> 26:24.760
We should talk to you first.

26:24.760 --> 26:26.840
Ommmm.

26:29.600 --> 26:33.760
Now I feel really bad
about what happened yesterday.

26:33.760 --> 26:36.280
You weren't to know, Cat.

26:36.280 --> 26:39.480
She wasn't always such a cow.

26:39.480 --> 26:43.040
When I first met Susie,
she was great fun.

26:43.040 --> 26:45.200
The five of us
had such a mad time

26:45.200 --> 26:47.160
starting that band together.

26:47.160 --> 26:48.760
[ Mid-tempo rock music plays]

26:48.760 --> 26:52.960
♪ Keep things a mystery♪

26:54.480 --> 26:59.000
♪ You know they have history♪

27:02.120 --> 27:07.360
♪ And, no,
it never ends well♪

27:07.360 --> 27:11.360
♪ It's called death by vinyl♪

27:18.840 --> 27:20.800
I remember you two
laughing a lot.

27:23.440 --> 27:25.320
How was she killed?

27:25.320 --> 27:28.600
Strangled with
a microphone cord.

27:28.600 --> 27:31.200
[ Gasps ]

27:31.200 --> 27:34.400
You know Volcanic Youth
had a song called "Strangled"?

27:34.400 --> 27:37.440
-Have you got it?
-No.

27:37.440 --> 27:41.080
I made a point of not buying the
albums after I quit the band.

27:41.080 --> 27:43.120
I think
we should take a listen.

27:47.000 --> 27:49.160
What time did your wife leave?

27:49.160 --> 27:53.640
Well, I carried on drinking
till about 2:00.

27:53.640 --> 27:58.400
Then I went back up to the room
and we argued some more,

27:58.400 --> 28:02.880
[Sniffs] and then she drove off
about 20 past.

28:02.880 --> 28:04.120
Any idea of her destination?

28:07.080 --> 28:09.000
Were you and Electra Bliss
having an affair?

28:09.000 --> 28:11.200
You're joking, aren't you?

28:13.360 --> 28:16.080
It's bad enough being married
to oneof them.

28:17.840 --> 28:19.560
No.

28:19.560 --> 28:21.600
Purely professional
between us.

28:23.520 --> 28:26.040
[ Door opens ]

28:26.040 --> 28:29.720
Hey, Pat. You got a copy
of "Twenty Seven"?

28:29.720 --> 28:32.760
Course I have, Cat.

28:38.400 --> 28:40.480
-There you go.
-Cheers.

28:47.960 --> 28:51.560
♪ Scream and shout
my angry words♪

28:51.560 --> 28:54.880
♪ A song
you just can't handle♪

28:54.880 --> 28:58.640
♪ Before I clench
my steel guitar♪

28:58.640 --> 29:01.760
♪ This voice
cannot be strangled♪

29:01.760 --> 29:04.600
Any issues going on
with the band?

29:04.600 --> 29:07.720
There's always issues
with the band.

29:07.720 --> 29:09.240
Care to elaborate?

29:10.640 --> 29:11.880
Well...

29:13.040 --> 29:15.960
...Electra demanded
that I get in a session drummer

29:15.960 --> 29:17.520
to replace Viv.

29:17.520 --> 29:20.040
She wanted her out.

29:22.080 --> 29:23.600
[ Backmasked vocals]

29:29.600 --> 29:31.640
[ Backmasked vocals]

29:31.640 --> 29:34.000
You hear that?

29:34.000 --> 29:35.160
Don't remember that
on the radio.

29:35.160 --> 29:38.360
-What was it?
-Backmasking.

29:38.360 --> 29:40.560
It's a technique
where you record lyrics

29:40.560 --> 29:43.200
backwards onto a track that's
going to be played forwards,

29:43.200 --> 29:44.480
so the only way
you can hear the words

29:44.480 --> 29:47.040
is to spin the record
in reverse.

29:47.040 --> 29:48.760
♪ Carry your sin♪

29:48.760 --> 29:52.520
♪ Through the moonlit wood♪

29:52.520 --> 29:55.120
Okay, so that's not weird
at all.

29:58.040 --> 30:00.560
-This was mixed by Kurt Lee.
-Yeah.

30:00.560 --> 30:04.160
He's the sound engineer
I met up at Trent Farm.

30:14.840 --> 30:16.000
Let's start with the accident.

30:17.200 --> 30:19.280
Accident?

30:19.280 --> 30:21.280
What?

30:21.280 --> 30:24.120
What do you mean?
Am I under arrest?

30:24.120 --> 30:26.840
If -- I-If I --
Well, then, I need Len.

30:26.840 --> 30:27.880
Or I need a solicitor.

30:27.880 --> 30:29.160
Did you run over this dog

30:29.160 --> 30:30.720
on your way to the studio
yesterday?

30:30.720 --> 30:31.720
[ Tires screech, dog yelps]

30:31.720 --> 30:33.240
[ Crash, dog whimpers]

30:33.240 --> 30:35.080
I don't know
what you're on about.

30:35.080 --> 30:38.240
I-I thought we were here
about Susan.

30:38.240 --> 30:40.760
I mean, I can't believe
she's dead, do you know,

30:40.760 --> 30:42.560
and murdered to boot.

30:42.560 --> 30:44.720
She's been my friend
for 40-odd years.

30:44.720 --> 30:49.280
Did you know she wanted you
replaced by a session drummer?

30:49.280 --> 30:51.080
No.

30:51.160 --> 30:52.880
No.

30:52.880 --> 30:54.560
I didn't.

31:26.160 --> 31:27.760
[ Engine starts ]

31:31.920 --> 31:34.200
No one else arrived or left

31:34.200 --> 31:38.160
until the cleaner turned up
at 8:00 a.m.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.920
And your aunts are here.

31:46.800 --> 31:48.720
Please don't tell anyone.

31:54.960 --> 31:57.320
No.
No, no, no, no, no.

31:57.320 --> 31:58.760
If Inspector Thorne
finds out you're here...

31:58.760 --> 32:00.000
You need to leave.

32:00.000 --> 32:01.560
Mattie, we might have
something on the case.

32:01.560 --> 32:03.880
You can't be involved --
especially as you knew her

32:03.880 --> 32:06.320
and apparently had a fight
with her only yesterday.

32:06.320 --> 32:09.440
Look, kid.
Susie was strangled, correct?

32:09.440 --> 32:10.640
Well, guess what the last song

32:10.640 --> 32:11.920
on their breakup album
was called.

32:11.920 --> 32:14.000
I'm gonna go for "Strangled."

32:14.000 --> 32:16.240
No such thing
as a bad coincidence.

32:16.240 --> 32:17.600
CAT:
And it was mixed by Kurt Lee.

32:17.600 --> 32:19.400
Tell her about
the backmasking.

32:19.400 --> 32:21.640
We listened to "Strangled"
on vinyl.

32:21.640 --> 32:24.000
The band recorded
a secret message

32:24.000 --> 32:25.720
at the end
of the song backwards.

32:25.720 --> 32:28.040
"Carry your sin
through a moonlit wood."

32:28.040 --> 32:29.320
And?

32:29.320 --> 32:30.640
It's rather sinister,
don't you think?

32:30.640 --> 32:33.480
A strange lyric at the end
of a 30-year-old song?

32:33.480 --> 32:35.120
It's hardly a motive
for murder.

32:35.120 --> 32:37.600
No, now, come on!
You need to leave.

32:37.600 --> 32:39.080
Go on.

32:39.960 --> 32:40.960
JANE: [ Sighs ]

32:40.960 --> 32:42.320
[ Engine starts ]

32:43.840 --> 32:45.480
Although she had dismissed it,

32:45.480 --> 32:49.400
this was exactly the sort
of obscure potential clue

32:49.400 --> 32:52.680
that would churn endlessly
around in Matilda's brain

32:52.680 --> 32:54.640
like the worst kind of earworm.

32:55.840 --> 32:58.080
I owe it to Susie
to look into this.

32:59.720 --> 33:01.960
Don't stop,
or Mattie might see me.

33:10.720 --> 33:13.760
Cat's eventful year
as a Hollywood stuntwoman

33:13.760 --> 33:15.600
had stayed with her.

33:15.600 --> 33:18.240
Known amongst that close-knit
community of thrill seekers

33:18.240 --> 33:20.080
as "Nine Lives,"

33:20.080 --> 33:23.080
had it not been for an aversion
to health-food fads

33:23.080 --> 33:25.400
and a yearning
for actual seasons,

33:25.400 --> 33:27.240
she may well have
settled permanently

33:27.240 --> 33:30.000
in the City of Angels.

33:30.640 --> 33:33.280
I understand you gave Susan
the studio keys.

33:33.280 --> 33:36.040
Yeah, she knocked on my door
about 2:00 asking for them.

33:36.040 --> 33:39.760
Said the muse was in her
and she wanted to record alone.

33:39.760 --> 33:42.080
So you were the last person
to see her alive.

33:42.080 --> 33:44.720
Well, I guess.

33:44.720 --> 33:46.320
Except for the murderer.

33:51.600 --> 33:54.280
-Hmm.
-What do you see?

33:55.800 --> 33:58.200
Well, Susan set it up
for vocals.

33:58.200 --> 33:59.920
Was anything recorded?

33:59.920 --> 34:03.080
Um, I don't know.

34:03.080 --> 34:06.440
But the tape's been taken.

34:06.440 --> 34:09.360
There was a reel
on there yesterday.

34:10.600 --> 34:12.000
[ Line ringing ]

34:12.000 --> 34:13.280
[ Beep]

34:13.280 --> 34:14.600
TYNE:
You've reached the office

34:14.600 --> 34:17.159
of Steven W. Tyne
at Retrodisc Records,

34:17.159 --> 34:18.679
Please leave a message.

34:18.679 --> 34:20.320
[ Beep]

34:20.320 --> 34:23.239
Uh, Steven, hi.
It's Len Savage again.

34:23.239 --> 34:27.000
Um, obviously,
under the circumstances,

34:27.000 --> 34:29.199
it's, uh, it's -- it's really
urgent that we speak,

34:29.199 --> 34:31.560
so call me back.

34:31.560 --> 34:34.560
Okay. Um...

34:34.560 --> 34:36.159
Bye-bye.

34:38.199 --> 34:41.400
MATILDA: You were the engineer
on "Twenty Seven."

34:41.400 --> 34:43.960
At the end of "Strangled,"
there's a backmasked lyric --

34:43.960 --> 34:45.880
"Carry your sin
through a moonlit wood."

34:45.880 --> 34:47.400
What was that about?

34:48.920 --> 34:51.360
Sorry, it's a long time ago now.
I really don't remember.

34:53.159 --> 34:55.719
Are there hidden messages
on other albums?

34:55.719 --> 34:57.880
I didn't kill her.

35:00.920 --> 35:05.960
Susan was spectacular
to listen to.

35:05.960 --> 35:08.840
You know, not just singing,
but talking.

35:08.840 --> 35:11.200
Even breathing.

35:11.200 --> 35:15.400
She'd whisper a lyric
or shout it or make a sound

35:15.400 --> 35:19.720
that just, you know,
connected right here,

35:19.720 --> 35:23.960
like she'd reached in
and -- and grabbed your heart.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.880
You know, it's what
great singers can do.

35:30.880 --> 35:34.160
Can make you feel something.

35:34.160 --> 35:37.280
You know, I would never
rob the world of that.

35:55.960 --> 35:57.000
[ Door opens ]

36:26.600 --> 36:30.000
JANE: Isn't that
their missing keyboardist?

36:30.000 --> 36:32.040
Park up over there, Beth.

36:42.120 --> 36:44.680
-Mr. Ives.
-Ah.

36:44.680 --> 36:47.040
It's going to take
a lot of komiyam

36:47.040 --> 36:49.040
to balance out
the negative energy that

36:49.040 --> 36:50.680
the murder would have produced.

36:50.680 --> 36:51.880
Komiyam?

36:51.880 --> 36:55.800
Cow urine.
To rebless the property.

36:57.040 --> 36:59.880
Uh, I need to ask you
some questions.

36:59.880 --> 37:01.440
Did you know Electra Bliss

37:01.440 --> 37:03.400
prior to Volcanic Youth
coming to record here?

37:03.400 --> 37:05.840
-Only by reputation.
-And how was she at the dinner?

37:05.840 --> 37:08.160
Exactly as you'd imagine.

37:08.160 --> 37:12.560
A complete diva with highly
narcissistic tendencies.

37:12.560 --> 37:15.080
Didn't warm to her, then,
Mr. Ives?

37:15.080 --> 37:17.480
You don't warm to rock stars.

37:17.480 --> 37:21.480
They expect everyone
to be in their orbit.

37:21.480 --> 37:23.840
And it's Sir Ray,
by the way.

37:23.840 --> 37:26.040
Sorry, Sir Ray.
Of course it is.

37:26.040 --> 37:28.240
Truth is...

37:29.960 --> 37:32.120
...Volcanic Youth
weren't much of a band

37:32.120 --> 37:35.200
after they lost their original
singer, Nikki Holler.

37:36.400 --> 37:40.560
For my money,
she was the talented one.

37:40.560 --> 37:42.280
GINA: Oi, Len.

37:42.280 --> 37:44.480
No way are you
getting out of this.

37:44.480 --> 37:46.280
It's not my responsibility.

37:46.280 --> 37:48.200
GINA: These people
do not mess about, okay?

37:48.200 --> 37:49.840
We need to pay them
what she owed.

37:49.840 --> 37:51.920
That's your problem, Gina.

37:51.920 --> 37:53.920
It's not mine.

37:53.920 --> 37:56.480
One call, it's gonna be
your problem too.

37:59.800 --> 38:04.120
I take it you had keys to the
studio and Electra Bliss' room?

38:05.960 --> 38:09.040
You keen on DIYs, Sir Ray?

38:09.040 --> 38:12.040
I try to do as much of
the maintenance here as I can.

38:12.040 --> 38:13.520
I like my privacy.

38:13.520 --> 38:15.920
Why do you ask?
Need a hand putting up a shelf?

38:15.920 --> 38:17.120
No.

38:18.280 --> 38:20.280
I think someone was keeping
a rather close eye

38:20.280 --> 38:21.600
on the deceased.

38:32.000 --> 38:34.720
-Look.
-Oh, not another one?

38:34.720 --> 38:36.320
We mustn't let Mattie see them.

38:38.280 --> 38:39.440
[ Door opens ]

38:43.480 --> 38:44.600
JANE: Oh.

38:48.800 --> 38:50.400
Where is she off to now?

38:50.400 --> 38:51.960
BETH: Shh.
She'll hear us.

38:51.960 --> 38:53.040
JANE:
Well, why has she stopped?

38:57.600 --> 38:59.040
Did Len send you?

38:59.040 --> 39:01.240
No, we're Cat Stone's sisters.

39:01.240 --> 39:03.640
-People are looking for you.
-Tough.

39:03.640 --> 39:05.520
They'll have to
record the album without me.

39:05.520 --> 39:08.040
Album?
Electra Bliss is dead.

39:08.040 --> 39:10.120
She was murdered last night
in the studio.

39:10.120 --> 39:12.200
Go on.

39:12.200 --> 39:14.320
Tallulah Savage-Hughes,
you're under arrest.

39:14.320 --> 39:15.840
-Citizen's.
-What?

39:15.840 --> 39:18.000
You're supposed to say, "I am
making a citizen's arrest."

39:18.000 --> 39:19.320
[ Cellphone powers on,
chiming ]

39:19.320 --> 39:21.880
-I'm making a...
-Yes.

39:21.880 --> 39:24.440
What's the point of that?
You're coming with us.

39:24.440 --> 39:25.840
[ Chiming continues ]

39:28.840 --> 39:31.120
LEN:
Give it a rest, Jonas.

39:32.280 --> 39:34.480
TALLULAH: See you've still
got the jacket.

39:34.480 --> 39:37.960
ELECTRA: One previous owner --
Janis Joplin.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.400
I got it when "Twenty Seven"

39:39.400 --> 39:41.040
reached number three
in the charts.

39:41.040 --> 39:44.000
So where's the jacket now?

39:44.000 --> 39:45.560
Perhaps the killer took it.

39:46.600 --> 39:48.080
[ Telephone rings ]

39:50.760 --> 39:52.360
D.S. Matilda Stone.

39:52.360 --> 39:54.760
BETH: Mattie, I know we're
not meant to get involved,

39:54.760 --> 39:56.200
but we found Tallulah
in town.

39:56.200 --> 39:59.000
And we're bringing her in.

39:59.000 --> 40:01.720
I'll meet you outside.

40:02.360 --> 40:03.960
Tell me that wasn't
one of your aunts.

40:03.960 --> 40:07.400
That wasn't one of my aunts.

40:07.400 --> 40:11.280
Technically,
Matilda wasn't lying.

40:13.720 --> 40:15.840
I spoke to the travel agency.

40:15.840 --> 40:18.120
They said you bought a ticket
to Brazil.

40:20.120 --> 40:22.880
-I'm leaving my husband.
-Seems like a long way to go.

40:22.880 --> 40:24.760
The further, the better.

40:26.120 --> 40:28.040
You had an argument
with the deceased

40:28.040 --> 40:30.120
a few hours
before her murder.

40:33.320 --> 40:36.720
Being in a band together
for over 30 years

40:36.720 --> 40:40.560
means we're
a highly dysfunctional family.

40:40.560 --> 40:42.280
At the start, we were equal.

40:42.280 --> 40:47.160
We'd flog the merch,
drive the van.

40:47.160 --> 40:48.640
We all chipped in.

40:48.640 --> 40:51.000
Well, that changed.

40:51.000 --> 40:54.800
For years now, Susan has had
the rest of us over a barrel.

40:54.800 --> 40:56.600
I just wanted out.

40:56.600 --> 40:58.440
Okay.

40:58.440 --> 41:01.320
So who else might have a motive
to kill her?

41:03.600 --> 41:05.080
I don't know about a motive,

41:05.080 --> 41:09.840
but you should be talking
to Viv.

41:09.840 --> 41:12.160
As I was driving off
last night,

41:12.160 --> 41:15.680
I saw her
going into the studio.

41:33.520 --> 41:35.360
I need to speak to the drummer.
Set up a room.

41:35.360 --> 41:36.800
I just want to
check something out first.

41:36.800 --> 41:38.840
Okay.

41:38.840 --> 41:40.400
Babe.

41:40.400 --> 41:43.320
Babe, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

41:43.320 --> 41:45.840
-Where have you been?
-None of your business.

41:45.840 --> 41:48.720
It's over, Len.
All of it.

41:48.720 --> 41:51.040
You don't get to
control me anymore.

42:23.000 --> 42:25.040
Oh! [ Sighs ]

42:25.040 --> 42:26.520
Aunt Cat,
what are you doing in here?

42:26.520 --> 42:28.760
Same as you.
Trying to solve this.

42:28.760 --> 42:30.680
But the door was...

42:30.680 --> 42:32.440
How did you get in here?

42:32.440 --> 42:33.720
What are you looking for?

42:33.720 --> 42:36.440
Ugh, Janis Joplin's jacket.

42:36.440 --> 42:39.600
Right. Okay.

42:39.600 --> 42:42.160
So now that Susan's murder
is trending on Twitter,

42:42.160 --> 42:44.520
we've got to get you lot into
the studio to record some music

42:44.520 --> 42:46.880
to go with the lyrics
she laid down last night.

42:46.880 --> 42:48.760
KURT:
You're out of luck, Len.

42:48.760 --> 42:50.320
Tape's missing.

42:50.320 --> 42:51.600
No, no, it isn't.

42:51.600 --> 42:53.720
I-I-I slipped it out
first thing this morning

42:53.720 --> 42:55.000
before they sealed the studio.

42:55.000 --> 42:57.600
But isn't that, like, evidence
or something?

42:57.600 --> 43:00.280
I mean, shouldn't you
hand it over to the police?

43:00.280 --> 43:03.640
Oh, guys!
Come on! It's just lyrics!

43:03.640 --> 43:06.960
We owe it to the memory of Susan
to record this.

43:06.960 --> 43:08.280
Ha!

43:08.280 --> 43:11.120
Now, where have
I heard that before?

43:14.760 --> 43:16.240
Something I want to show you.

43:22.080 --> 43:23.920
"I know you're drinking again.

43:23.920 --> 43:25.920
I won't let your inability
to deal with the past

43:25.920 --> 43:28.520
ruin our future."

43:28.520 --> 43:30.840
Viv lied to me.

43:30.840 --> 43:34.160
She did know Electra Bliss
wanted her out.

43:41.360 --> 43:43.040
[ Line ringing ]

43:43.040 --> 43:44.440
[ Beep]

43:44.440 --> 43:45.880
TYNE:
You've reached the office

43:45.880 --> 43:48.640
of Steven W. Tyne
at Retrodisc Records.

43:48.640 --> 43:49.680
Please leave a message.

43:49.680 --> 43:51.000
[ Beep]

43:51.000 --> 43:54.000
Steven, uh --
oh, it's like a bad joke.

43:54.000 --> 43:57.440
Um, how can you claim
to run a record company

43:57.440 --> 44:00.320
if you don't answer
your damn phone, huh?

44:00.320 --> 44:02.720
It's Len.
Savage.

44:02.720 --> 44:04.640
-[ Blade plunges ]
-[ Grunts ]

44:13.840 --> 44:16.640
[ Woman screams ]

44:16.640 --> 44:18.440
[ Screaming ]

44:24.680 --> 44:27.600
The method by which Len Savage
had been dispatched

44:27.600 --> 44:30.800
was not without wit,

44:30.800 --> 44:33.440
for Volcanic Youth's manager
had always been

44:33.440 --> 44:36.160
a rather enthusiastic
backstabber.

44:41.760 --> 44:45.600
♪ Keep things a mystery ♪

44:46.960 --> 44:52.120
♪ You know they have history ♪

44:54.560 --> 45:00.000
♪ And, no,
it never ends well ♪

45:00.000 --> 45:04.520
♪ It's called death by vinyl ♪
